<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-05T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-05T15:00:00-05:00" n="97" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3589: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Des Portes</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">La
                                            Paz</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-05T16:00:00-04:00">March 5, 1934—4
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>18. Foreign Minister Calvo has tendered resignation because of
                                disagreement regarding reply to peace proposal which may be made
                                tonight.</p>
                            <p>He desires this kept confidential presumably hoping for rejection
                                resignation and furtherance his peace efforts.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>